12/04/2011
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Emil Boc filed his candidacy Monday (April 11th) for another term at the helm of his Democratic Liberal Party (PDL). 
He will face his main rival, Vasile Blaga, currently PDL secretary general. 
The third candidate is former Culture Minister Theodor Paleologu. 
The PDL will hold its national convention on May 14th and 15th. 
(Ziare - 12/04/11; Hotnews.ro, Romania Libera, Cotidianul, Evenimentul Zilei, Realitatea - 11/04/11)
